<open_redirect_verification>
<validity_requirements>
For an open redirect claim to be VALID, you must independently verify:

1. EXTERNAL REDIRECT
   - Can redirect to fully external domain
   - NOT: Same-origin redirects only
   - Check: Does browser land on attacker-controlled site?

2. ATTACKER CONTROLS DESTINATION
   - Redirect URL is attacker-specified
   - NOT: Fixed redirect targets
   - Check: Can you specify https://evil.com?

3. PHISHING VIABILITY
   - Initial URL looks legitimate
   - NOT: Obvious malicious URL
   - Check: Would users trust the link?
</validity_requirements>

<independent_control_tests>
YOU MUST DESIGN YOUR OWN TESTS. Do not reproduce the reporter's tests.

TEST 1: EXTERNAL REDIRECT TEST
Purpose: Verify redirect to external domain
Steps:
1. Identify redirect parameter (url=, next=, redirect=)
2. Set to external: https://evil.com
3. Test bypass variations: //evil.com, ///evil.com
4. Verify browser lands on external domain

TEST 2: PHISHING VIABILITY
Purpose: Verify can be used for phishing
Steps:
1. Craft URL on target domain with redirect
2. Verify it looks legitimate
3. Confirm redirect lands on external site
</independent_control_tests>

<validity_decision_matrix>
| Redirect Target | Allowlist | Interstitial | Decision |
|----------------|-----------|--------------|----------|
| External domain | None | None | VULNERABLE |
| External domain | Present, bypassed | None | VULNERABLE |
| Same-origin only | Enforced | N/A | NOT VULNERABLE |
| External | Any | Warning shown | LIMITED impact |
</validity_decision_matrix>

<common_false_positive_patterns>
REJECT if you observe:
- Redirect only to same-origin paths
- Strict domain allowlist enforced
- Redirect requires authentication/confirmation
- Interstitial page warns about redirect
- Only relative paths accepted
</common_false_positive_patterns>
